Given an integer N, write a program to check if the number is a palindrome.
A palindrome number reads the same backward as forward.
If N is a negative number, it cannot be a palindrome. In such cases, print false.
Input Format

Given an integer N, write a program to check if the number is a palindrome.
A palindrome number reads the same backward as forward.
If N is a negative number, it cannot be a palindrome. In such cases, print false.
Constraints

-10^9 ≤ N ≤ 10^9
Output Format

Print true if the number is a palindrome, otherwise print false.
Sample Input 0

121
Sample Output 0

true
Sample Input 1

-121
Sample Output 1

false
Sample Input 2

100
Sample Output 2

false

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        if(n<0){
            System.out.println("false");
            return;
        }
        int temp=n;
        int r=0;
        while(n!=0){
            int m=n%10;
            r=(r*10)+m;
            n=n/10;
        }
        if(r==temp){
            System.out.println("true");
        }else{
            System.out.println("false");
        }
    }
}
